dy offers a full account of the poem, together with an edition of the text and facing translation. It aims to resolve some of the poem's vexing issues and provides a varietyof possible interpretations of the poem. The in-depth literary analysis seeks to enrich modern scholarly perceptions of the poem, suggest a more appropriate title, and contribute to continued scholarly discussion and analysis of the Exeter Book and its compilation. It provides a guide towards understanding the poem's main theme, presents the text in light of its position in ecclesiastical history, and sheds fresh light into its place and significance within the corpus of Old English poetry. M.R. Rambaran-Olm received her PhD from the University of Glasgow.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBaptism in literature. 0aChristian poetry, English (Old)xHistory and criticism. 4aHistory of Religion. 4aMedieval Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aDescent into Hell.  aExeter Book.  aJohn the Baptist's Prayer or The Descent into Hell from the Exeter Book: Text, Translation and Critical Study.  aM.R. Rambaran-Olm.  aOld English poem.  aOld English poetry.  aecclesiastical history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311143136940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178204200640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782042006423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782042006/original  a978-3-11-143136-9  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles